<DocsLayout title="Support" description="Public support paths for Silo integrations, incident follow-up, and privacy or deletion requests.">
  <h1>Support</h1>

  <p>Last updated: 2026-03-24</p>

  <p>This page describes the public support paths for Silo.</p>

  <h2>What support covers</h2>

  <p>Use this page for:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>API and MCP integration questions;</li>
    <li>reproducible bugs and degraded behavior;</li>
    <li>workflow troubleshooting;</li>
    <li>privacy or deletion requests;</li>
    <li>credential leakage or abuse reports.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Public support path</h2>

  <p>For non-sensitive requests, use the repository issue tracker:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/sensdiego/valter/issues">GitHub Issues for sensdiego/valter</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Private or sensitive requests</h2>

  <p>Do not post secrets, API keys, private case documents, or personal data in a public issue.</p>

  <p>If you already have a customer or onboarding channel, use that private path for:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>production incidents;</li>
    <li>privacy or deletion requests;</li>
    <li>credential rotation or revocation;</li>
    <li>sensitive legal workflow artifacts.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>If you do not already have a private support path, open a public issue with a minimal description and ask for a private follow-up.</p>

  <h2>What to include in a request</h2>

  <p>Including the items below makes support much faster:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><code>trace_id</code> from the failing response or log;</li>
    <li>timestamp and timezone;</li>
    <li>endpoint or MCP tool name;</li>
    <li>workflow ID, conversation ID, or artifact ID when applicable;</li>
    <li>whether the problem is reproducible;</li>
    <li>sanitized request payload or example input.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Response expectations</h2>

  <p>Support from this public page is best-effort. No contractual SLA is implied here unless a separate written agreement says otherwise.</p>

  <h2>Related pages</h2>

